<treatment id="03BA844365535C00FD0FCCBFFF21FC2D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03BA844365535C00FD0FCCBFFF21FC2D" httpUri="http://treatment.plazi.org/id/03BA844365535C00FD0FCCBFFF21FC2D" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="644" pageId="8" pageNumber="643">
<subSubSection id="C30966DE65535C00FD0FCCBFFF21FC2D" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="644" pageId="8" pageNumber="643" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAC355565535C01FD0FCCBFFB1BF935" blockId="8.[713,1248,1426,1705]" lastBlockId="8.[716,1247,1711,1737]" pageId="8" pageNumber="643">
While creating 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665535C01FCB4CCBFFB1BFA37" authority=", Thiele (1934: 878)" authorityName=", Thiele" authorityPageNumber="878" authorityYear="1934" box="[881,1247,1457,1483]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Microcardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="8" pageNumber="643" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967E94765535C01FCB4CCBFFBC1FA37" box="[881,1029,1457,1483]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="643">Microcardium</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8248A465535C01FBD1CCBFFB1BFA37" author="THIELE J." box="[1044,1247,1457,1483]" pageId="8" pageNumber="643" pagination="779 - 1022" refId="ref12980" refString="THIELE J. 1934. - Handbuch der systematischen Weichtierkunde. Zweiter Band. DritterTeil. Scaphopoda. Bivalvia. Cephalopoda. Fischer, Stuttgart: 779 - 1022." type="book chapter" year="1934">Thiele (1934: 878)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
failed to designate a 
<typeStatus id="54A88BF765535C01FC61CCDFFC16FA17" box="[932,978,1489,1515]" pageId="8" pageNumber="643">type</typeStatus>
species but recorded two species in his new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665535C01FC10CCFFFC41F9D7" authority="E. A. Smith, 1885" authorityName="E. A. Smith" authorityYear="1885" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="8" pageNumber="643" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="torresi" subGenus="Fragum">
<emphasis id="B967E94765535C01FC10CCFFFBF0F9F7" box="[981,1076,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="643">Cardium</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B967E94765535C01FB87CCFCFB56F9F7" box="[1090,1170,1522,1547]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="643">Fragum</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B967E94765535C01FB64CCFCFB24F9F7" box="[1185,1248,1522,1547]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="643">torresi</emphasis>
E. A. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8248A465535C01FCC6CF1FFC41F9D7" author="SMITH E. A." box="[771,901,1553,1579]" pageId="8" pageNumber="643" pagination="1 - 341" refId="ref12743" refString="SMITH E. A. 1885. - Report on the Lamellibranchiata collected by H. M. S. Challenger, during the years 1873 - 1876. Report on the Scientific Results of the Voyage of H. M. S. Challenger (Zool.) 13: 1 - 341, pls 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="1885">Smith, 1885</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665535C01FC70CF1EFB1CF9D6" authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1881" box="[949,1240,1552,1578]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="8" pageNumber="643" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="peramabilis" subGenus="Fulvia">
<emphasis id="B967E94765535C01FC70CF1EFBD5F9D6" box="[949,1041,1552,1578]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="643">Cardium</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B967E94765535C01FBDBCF1CFB9DF9D6" box="[1054,1113,1554,1578]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="643">Fulvia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B967E94765535C01FBA0CF1EFB1CF9D6" box="[1125,1240,1552,1578]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="643">peramabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Later, a 
<typeStatus id="54A88BF765535C01FCD8CF3EFC8FF9B6" box="[797,843,1584,1610]" pageId="8" pageNumber="643">type</typeStatus>
species was independently and almost simultaneously designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8248A465535C01FBE5CF5EFB19F996" author="KEEN A. M." box="[1056,1245,1616,1642]" pageId="8" pageNumber="643" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref11711" refString="KEEN A. M. 1937. - Nomenclatural units of the Pelecypod family Cardiidae. Bulletin du Museum royal d'Histoire naturelle de Belgique 13 (7): 1 - 22." type="journal article" year="1937">Keen (1937: 15)</bibRefCitation>
and by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8248A465535C01FCD9CF7EFBCAF976" author="DALL W. H. &amp; BARTSCH P. &amp; REHDER H. A." box="[796,1038,1648,1674]" pageId="8" pageNumber="643" pagination="1 - 233" refId="ref11444" refString="DALL W. H., BARTSCH P. &amp; REHDER H. A. 1938. - A manual of the recent Pelecypod mollusks of the Hawaiian Islands. Bulletin of the Bernice P. Bishop Museum 153: 1 - 233." type="journal article" year="1938">
Dall 
<emphasis id="B967E94765535C01FC95CF7EFCBFF976" box="[848,891,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="643">et al</emphasis>
. (1938: 153)
</bibRefCitation>
. Unfortunately, the latter authors chose Smith species, on the wrong 
<heading id="D0E4823965535C01FD09CFA1FB1BF935" box="[716,1247,1711,1737]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="8" pageNumber="643" reason="1">
basis that 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665535C01FCFBCFA1FC19F935" authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1881" box="[830,989,1711,1737]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="8" pageNumber="643" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="peramabilis">
<emphasis id="B967E94765535C01FCFBCFA1FC19F935" box="[830,989,1711,1737]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="643">C. peramabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was already attributed
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAC355565525C00FF6BC97DFED1FF78" blockId="9.[174,277,115,133]" box="[174,277,115,133]" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">Poutiers J.-M.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAC355565525C00FF52C9F0FDD7FCCE" blockId="9.[149,686,254,977]" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8248A465525C00FF7EC9F0FE86FEE4" author="DALL W. H." box="[187,322,254,280]" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" refId="ref11397" refString="DALL W. H. 1901. - Synopsis of the family Cardiidae" type="book" year="1901">Dall (1901)</bibRefCitation>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665525C00FEAEC9F0FD56FEE4" authority="Beyrich, 1845" authorityName="Beyrich" authorityYear="1845" box="[363,658,254,280]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Protocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967E94765525C00FEAEC9F0FE23FEE4" box="[363,487,254,280]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">Protocardia</emphasis>
Beyrich, 1845
</taxonomicName>
, a Mesozoic genus of different origin. Although this action is invalidated by Keen’s designation, it has undoubtedly contributed to misunderstand the true significance of 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665525C00FEF3C872FE0EFE6A" authorityName=", Thiele" authorityYear="1934" box="[310,458,380,406]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Microcardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967E94765525C00FEF3C872FE0EFE6A" box="[310,458,380,406]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">Microcardium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and to its confusion with 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665525C00FF14C892FD86FE4A" authority="(Habe 1951: 152)" baseAuthorityName="Habe" baseAuthorityPageNumber="152" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[209,578,412,438]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Frigidocardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967E94765525C00FF14C892FEB6FE4A" box="[209,370,412,438]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">Frigidocardium</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8248A465525C00FE47C892FDFEFE4A" author="HABE T." box="[386,570,412,438]" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" refId="ref11570" refString="HABE T. 1951. - Genera of Japanese Shells (1 &amp; 2). Pelecypoda and Scaphopoda. Kairui-bunken-kankokai, Kyoto, 186 p." type="book" year="1951">Habe 1951: 152</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
to which 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665525C00FF5CC8B2FF3FFE29" authorityName="E. A. Smith" authorityYear="1885" box="[153,251,444,470]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="torresi">
<emphasis id="B967E94765525C00FF5CC8B2FF3FFE29" box="[153,251,444,470]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">C. torresi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be attributed. Thiele’s genus can be easily recognized from 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665525C00FE7AC8D5FDA1FE09" baseAuthorityName="Habe" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[447,613,475,501]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Frigidocardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967E94765525C00FE7AC8D5FDA1FE09" box="[447,613,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">Frigidocardium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its heterogeneous sculpture (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8248A465525C00FE68C8F5FD45FDE9" author="POUTIERS J. - M." box="[429,641,507,533]" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" refId="ref12018" refString="POUTIERS J. - M. 1992. - The Australasian Protocardiinae" type="book" year="1992">Poutiers 1992: 142</bibRefCitation>
), its outer surface being divided in two strongly distinct sculptural areas, with spines restricted to the posterior one. Then, 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665525C00FECECB54FEACFD88" authorityName="Noda" authorityYear="1988" box="[267,360,602,628]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Tobarum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967E94765525C00FECECB54FEACFD88" box="[267,360,602,628]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">Tobarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot stand in 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665525C00FDD5CB54FD68FD88" baseAuthorityName="Habe" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[528,684,602,628]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Frigidocardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967E94765525C00FDD5CB54FD68FD88" box="[528,684,602,628]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">Frigidocardium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as originally proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8248A465525C00FE5BCB74FD94FD68" author="NODA H." box="[414,592,634,660]" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" pagination="29 - 85" refId="ref11880" refString="NODA H. 1988. - Molluscan fossils from the Ryukyu Islands, Southwest Japan. Part 2. Gastropoda and Pelecypoda from the Shinzato Formation in the middle part of Okinawa-jima. Science Reports of the Institute of Geosciences, University of Tsukuba (B) 9: 29 - 85." type="journal article" year="1988">Noda (1988: 74)</bibRefCitation>
, but falls within 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665525C00FF25CB97FEAAFD4F" authorityName=", Thiele" authorityYear="1934" box="[224,366,665,691]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Microcardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967E94765525C00FF25CB97FEAAFD4F" box="[224,366,665,691]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">Microcardium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665525C00FEBCCB97FF14FD2F" authority="Fischer-Piette, 1977" authorityName="Fischer-Piette" authorityYear="1977" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Decussicardium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967E94765525C00FEBCCB97FDD1FD4F" box="[377,533,665,691]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">Decussicardium</emphasis>
Fischer-Piette, 1977
</taxonomicName>
, invalidly introduced for the South African species 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665525C00FF23CBD7FD68FD0F" authority="G. B. Sowerby III, 1904" authorityName="G. B. Sowerby III" authorityYear="1904" box="[230,684,729,755]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gilchristi">
<emphasis id="B967E94765525C00FF23CBD7FE60FD0F" box="[230,420,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">Cardium gilchristi</emphasis>
G. B. Sowerby 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8248A465525C00FD8ECBD7FD68FD0F" author="SOWERBY G. B. III" box="[587,684,729,755]" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" pagination="1 - 19" refId="ref12865" refString="SOWERBY G. B. III 1904. - Mollusca of South Africa (Pelecypoda). Marine Investigations in South Africa 4: 1 - 19, pls 6 - 7." type="journal article" year="1904">III, 1904</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8248A465525C00FF02CBF7FE87FCEF" author="KEEN A. M." box="[199,323,761,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref11848" refString="KEEN A. M. 1980. - The Pelecypod family Cardiidae: a taxonomic summary. Tulane Studies in Geology and Paleontology 16 (1): 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1980">Keen 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8248A465525C00FE8ACBF7FD41FCEF" author="VOSKUIL R. P. A. &amp; ONVERWAGT W. J. H." box="[335,645,761,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" pagination="115 - 122" refId="ref13041" refString="VOSKUIL R. P. A. &amp; ONVERWAGT W. J. H. 1991. - Studies on Cardiidae. 5. The taxa introduced by E. Fischer- Piette in his &quot; Revision des Cardiidae &quot;. Basteria 55: 115 - 122." type="journal article" year="1991">Voskuil &amp; Onverwagt 1991</bibRefCitation>
), is another synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665525C00FEBDCA16FDC8FCCE" authorityName=", Thiele" authorityYear="1934" box="[376,524,792,818]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Microcardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967E94765525C00FEBDCA16FDC8FCCE" box="[376,524,792,818]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">Microcardium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAC355565525C00FF6BCA36FF21FC2D" blockId="9.[149,686,254,977]" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">
In the Recent fauna, 
<taxonomicName id="4C134ED665525C00FE5ACA36FDF3FCAE" authorityName=", Thiele" authorityYear="1934" box="[415,567,824,850]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Microcardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967E94765525C00FE5ACA36FDF3FCAE" box="[415,567,824,850]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="644">Microcardium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed on both sides of tropical America (for basic informations in this area, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8248A465525C00FE1FCA79FDA3FC6D" author="OLSSON A. A." box="[474,615,887,913]" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" refId="ref11933" refString="OLSSON A. A. 1961. - Mollusks of the Tropical Eastern Pacific, Particularly from the Southern Half of the Panamic-Pacific Faunal Province (Panama to Peru). Panamic-Pacific Pelecypoda. Paleontological Research Institution, Ithaca, 574 p., 86 pls." type="book" year="1961">Olsson 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8248A465525C00FDB0CA79FF15FC4D" author="KEEN A. M." pageId="9" pageNumber="644" refId="ref11808" refString="KEEN A. M. 1971. - Sea Shells of Tropical West America. Marine Mollusks from Baja California to Peru. Second edition. Stanford University, Stanford, xiv + 1064 p., 22 pls." type="book" year="1971">Keen 1971</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8248A465525C00FF19CA99FEADFC4D" author="ABBOTT R. T." box="[220,361,919,945]" pageId="9" pageNumber="644" refId="ref10960" refString="ABBOTT R. T. 1974. - American Seashells. The Marine Mollusca of the Atlantic and Pacific Coasts of North America. Second Edition. Van Nostrand Reinhold, New York, 663 p., 24 pls." type="book" year="1974">Abbott 1974</bibRefCitation>
), in addition to the Indo-West Pacific.
</paragraph>
